      • entryIDListFromDatabase

        public static long[] entryIDListFromDatabase(byte[] bytes)
        Decode an array of entry ID values from its database representation.
        Parameters:
        bytes - The raw database value, null if there is no value and hence no entry IDs. Note that this method will throw an ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException if the bytes array length is not a multiple of 8.
        Returns:
        An array of entry ID values.

      • dnFromDNKey

        public static DN dnFromDNKey(byte[] dnKey,
             int offset,
             int length,
             DN prefix)
                      throws DirectoryException
        Decode a DN value from its database key representation.
        Parameters:
        dnKey - The database key value of the DN.
        offset - Starting position in the database key data.
        length - The length of the database key data.
        prefix - The DN to prefix the deocded DN value.
        Returns:
        The decoded DN value.
        Throws:
        DirectoryException - if an error occurs while decoding the DN value.

      • findDNKeyParent

        public static int findDNKeyParent(byte[] dnKey,
                  int offset,
                  int length)
        Find the length of bytes that represents the superior DN of the given DN key. The superior DN is represented by the initial bytes of the DN key.
        Parameters:
        dnKey - The database key value of the DN.
        offset - Starting position in the database key data.
        length - The length of the database key data.
        Returns:
        The length of the superior DN or -1 if the given dn is the root DN or 0 if the superior DN is removed.

      • dnToDNKey

        public static byte[] dnToDNKey(DN dn,
               int prefixRDNs)
        Create a DN database key from an entry DN.
        Parameters:
        dn - The entry DN.
        prefixRDNs - The number of prefix RDNs to remove from the encoded representation.
        Returns:
        A DatabaseEntry containing the key.
